Creston first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0617232|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715024316/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0617232|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA – Creston CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Creston had a population of 94. The population density was {{convert|165.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Creston was 89 (94.7%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 2 (2.1%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1 (1.1%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0 (0.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2 (2.1%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 6 persons (6.4%).

The Census reported that 94 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 36 households, out of which 15 (41.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 20 (55.6%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 3 (8.3%) had a female householder with no husband present, 3 (8.3%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 3 (8.3%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (2.8%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 8 households (22.2%) were made up of individuals, and 2 (5.6%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.61.  There were 26 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (72.2% of all households); the average family size was 2.96.

The population was spread out, with 22 people (23.4%) under the age of 18, 4 people (4.3%) aged 18 to 24, 28 people (29.8%) aged 25 to 44, 27 people (28.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 13 people (13.8%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 39.0 years. For every 100 females, there were 80.8 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 80.0 males.

There were 39 housing units at an average density of {{convert|68.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 27 (75.0%) were owner-occupied, and 9 (25.0%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0%; the rental vacancy rate was 0%.  64 people (68.1% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 30 people (31.9%) lived in rental housing units.

